# Question 1 - Text Encryption and Decryption

## What this program does
This program reads a text file called raw_text.txt, encrypts it using
a custom encryption method, then decrypts it and verifies the result
matches the original.

## How to Run
Open terminal in this folder and type:

    python3 Question1.py

When prompted enter two shift values for example 2 and 3.

## Encryption Rules

### Lowercase letters
- Letters a to m are shifted forward by shift1 multiplied by shift2
- Letters n to z are shifted backward by shift1 plus shift2

### Uppercase letters
- Letters A to M are shifted backward by shift1
- Letters N to Z are shifted forward by shift2 squared

### Other characters
- Spaces, numbers, and symbols stay unchanged

## Files
- raw_text.txt — original input text
- encrypted_text.txt — generated after encryption
- decrypted_text.txt — generated after decryption

## Helper Functions
- shift_forward — shifts a lowercase letter forward
- shift_backward — shifts a lowercase letter backward
- shift_forward_upper — shifts an uppercase letter forward
- shift_backward_upper — shifts an uppercase letter backward

## Verification
After decryption the program automatically checks if the decrypted
text matches the original and prints the result.
